        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The request object facilitates and encapsulates access to global variables like $_POST, $_GET etc. \n\nFor some reason it does however _not_ support access to the content of the $_FILES variable, which is used when uploading files via a form. \n\nOf course a user can extend the Zend_Controller_Request_Http object to get that functionality, but I believe that in this case it should be part of the framework."
        },
